# Axis — Cursor Agent Rules

## Project overview
React + Vite web app for Axis Seattle shared housing. Deployed on Vercel/Netlify. Uses Supabase for data, Stripe for payments, Airtable for some features.

## Stack
- React 18 (JSX, no TypeScript)
- Vite (vite.config.mjs)
- Tailwind CSS v3 (tailwind.config.cjs)
- React Router v6
- Framer Motion for animations
- Supabase (auth + DB)
- Stripe (checkout, portal)
- Leaflet / React-Leaflet for maps
- react-hot-toast for notifications

## Project structure
- `src/pages/` — page-level components (Home, PropertyPage, Contact, Apply, etc.)
- `src/components/` — reusable UI components
- `src/data/properties.js` — all property/room data (source of truth)
- `src/lib/` — utility modules (seo.js, pricing.js, airtable.js, leaseTemplate.js)
- `src/utils/` — small helpers (scrollToTop.js)
- `api/` — Vercel serverless functions
- `netlify/functions/` — Netlify serverless functions
- `public/` — static assets

## Conventions
- No TypeScript — plain JSX throughout
- Tailwind utility classes only; avoid inline styles except for dynamic values
- Brand color: `#2563eb` (blue), accent: `#0ea5e9` (axis teal)
- `text-axis` / `bg-axis` utility classes map to the brand blue
- Framer Motion variants pattern: define `container`/`item` at module level, not inline
- `import React` is NOT needed — Vite uses automatic JSX runtime
- Lazy-load page components with `React.lazy` + `Suspense`
- All property data lives in `src/data/properties.js` — never hardcode property details elsewhere
- API routes use plain `fetch`, no axios

## Style guidelines
- Short, direct copy — no marketing fluff or redundant headings
- Section eyebrows use `text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-slate-500`
- Buttons: rounded-full, slate-900 bg for primary, border-slate-300 for secondary
- Cards: `rounded-[18px]` or `rounded-[28px]`, `border border-slate-200`

## Commands
- Dev: `npm run dev` (port 5173)
- Build: `npm run build`
- Preview: `npm run preview`

## Important notes
- Do not change external API signatures in `api/` without updating the corresponding frontend calls
- `src/data/properties.js` is the single source of truth for all listing data
- Mobile sticky CTA is in PropertyPage.jsx — keep it in sync with desktop sidebar pricing
- Supabase keys are in environment variables — never hardcode
